The British Virgin Islands authorities have introduced a number of precautionary measures in response to the coronavirus (COVID-19) pandemic.
With effect from Thursday 19th March, the Government of the Virgin Islands have prohibited all entry by sea or air by all visitors who are not nationals, Belongers, work permit holders or persons ordinarily resident in the Territory, or their dependents. The travel restriction will not apply to flight crews, diplomats or freight, cargo or courier craft or vessels. Further information on BVI travel advice can be found at the website of the Government of the Virgin Islands.
Travel restrictions have been put in place at all airports and seaports by the Government of the Virgin Islands. The Government has announced that they are limiting international ports of entry to Terrance B Lettsome International Airport (Beef Island), Road Town Ferry Terminal and Sopers Hole, West End, Tortola to enable enhanced screening procedures of all arriving passengers.
Further information on risks to travellers, avoidance measures, symptoms and how to self-quarantine is available on the BVI Ministry of Health and Social Development website.
With effect from Thursday 19th March, all schools, pre-schools and day-care centres will be closed for an initial period of 14 days. Additionally, for a period of 30 days from Thursday 19th March, all social gatherings including faith-based, sporting, cultural, recreational and commercial activities and other non-essential events are advised to restrict their numbers to a limit of 30 persons at a time, and a maximum of 10 people for those in vulnerable categories.
A decision has been made to postpone the BVI Spring Regatta and the Virgin Gorda Easter Festival.
British nationals wishing to leave the British Virgin Islands should make arrangements to do so as soon as possible.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
